{{Infobox book | name =Shakespeare and the Goddess of Complete Being | image = Shakespeare and the Goddess of Complete Being.jpg | author = [[Ted Hughes]] | country = United Kingdom | genre = [[Literary criticism]] | publisher = Faber Paperbacks | release_date = 1st edition (April 13, 1992) | pages = 524 | isbn = 978-0571166046 }}
'''''Shakespeare and the Goddess of Complete Being''''' is a book of [[literary criticism]] authored by [[Ted Hughes]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.publishersweekly.com/978-0-374-26204-4 |title=Fiction Review: Shakespeare and the Goddess of Complete Being by Ted Hughes|publisher=Publishersweekly.com |date=1992-08-31 |accessdate=2013-09-06}}</ref> Hughes has extensively discussed the poems and other literary works of [[Shakespeare]] in this book. The book is written in three parts: * Part one: ''The Immature Phase of the Tragic Equation'', * Part two: ''The Evolution of the Tragic Equation through the Seven Tragedies'' * Part three: ''The Transformation of the Tragic Equation in the Last Plays''<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ted-hughes.info/bibliographies/full-bibliography/bibliography-details/shakespeare-and-the-goddess-of-complete-being.html |title=Earth-Moon: Information about Ted Hughes: Shakespeare and the Goddess of Complete Being |publisher=Ted-hughes.info |date= |accessdate=2013-09-06}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news | url=https://www.lrb.co.uk/v14/n07/tom-paulin/protestant-guilt | title=Protestant Guilt| pages=10–11| newspaper=London Review of Books| date=1992-04-09| last1=Paulin| first1=Tom}}</ref> The book also provides an insight into Ted Hughes' gender attitudes.<ref>{{Cite book | doi=10.1007/978-1-349-27659-2_4|chapter = Ted Hughes and the Goddess of Complete Being|title = The Male Image| pages=67–93|year = 1999|last1 = Gregson|first1 = Ian| isbn=978-1-349-27661-5}}</ref>
